snippet.textDisplay: Colin I'd love to blast your choice of music in the daytime because I like it too, but if I'm watching at night and trying not to disturb the family I've either got to fuss with the volume to hear you speaking or get unpleasant eardrum surprises while wearing headphones. I'd love it if you sort of equalized the volume when editing your videos. When you fire up a jet engine and say it's going to be loud, it isn't even one-tenth as loud as the video's music. Your camera mic is like a grandma in the passing lane and your music is like a formula 1 car.
